com.adobe.livecycle.rightsmanagement.client.infomodel
Interface Permission

public interface Permission

The Permission interface defines the constants that represent the different types of policy permissions. The getName() method provides a way to retrieve the name of the type given the constant. PolicyEntry objects require Permission objects as parameters when adding or removing permissions to policy entries. To see this interface used in a code example, see the Creating a new policy using the Java API quick start in Programming with Adobe Experience Manager Forms.
